# Auto-detect text files and normalize them to LF in the working tree on
# checkout, regardless of each contributor's global git config.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must use LF line endings — a CRLF on the shebang line makes
# the kernel look for "/bin/bash\r" and fail with "bad interpreter".
*.sh text eol=lf

# The DEMOS array is a per-PR-append-only registry (each feature PR adds one
# row for its own demo clip), so two PRs adding adjacent rows is an additive
# conflict, not a genuine either/or -- git's built-in union merge driver takes
# both sides' lines automatically instead of producing conflict markers. Don't
# apply this more broadly: most other recurring-conflict files in this repo
# (demos/demo.json, website/tactics.qmd, FarTierRules.gd docstrings) need
# understanding-based consolidation, not a naive line union.
website/tools/record-demos.sh merge=union
